originalText.text:
Stay away from this place by all means. They upcharge you at the end with a +$10 surcharge, then the people parking the cars just don't care. While waiting for my car they nearly crashed into each other like 3 times. Then on top of all that they are nasty and rude.
STAY AWAY!

originalText.text: Are you seeking for your car to be stacked like sardines by greedy parking lot owners?  Are you also seeking to get double-charged?  I would suggest then you go to the Quik Park garage at 600 W 42nd Street where they charged me $52 twice after they said they would not.  It's apparent that parking lot owners which would stack your cars in the way shown by the attached photos are likely to be corrupt and crooked.

originalText.text:
Extremely Disappointed with Poor Service and Attitude

Rating: ★☆☆☆☆

I recently booked a parking spot online at this particular parking lot, hoping for a smooth and hassle-free experience. Unfortunately, my encounter with the staff left me utterly dissatisfied. The service I received was nothing short of terrible, and the attendant's unprofessional attitude only added to my frustration.

Upon arrival, I approached the attendant and explained that I had already paid for a parking spot online. Instead of offering any assistance or attempting to resolve the issue, the attendant immediately began displaying an excessive amount of attitude. It was as if I had inconvenienced him simply by asking for help.

To my disbelief, the attendant bluntly informed me that there were no available parking spots, despite the fact that I had already made a reservation and paid in advance. This unexpected turn of events not only resulted in missing my appointment but also left me feeling deeply disappointed and aggravated.

The lack of effort on the attendant's part to rectify the situation and find a satisfactory resolution was disheartening. His dismissive behavior and complete disregard for customer service were simply unacceptable. As a paying customer, I expected a level of professionalism and assistance that was sorely lacking during my visit.

In conclusion, my experience at this parking lot was undeniably the worst I have ever encountered. The combination of terrible service, unhelpful staff, and a complete lack of concern for customers' needs left me frustrated and dissatisfied. I strongly advise against utilizing this parking lot if you value quality service and a positive customer experience.

Please note that this review reflects my personal experience and opinion during my visit to the parking lot. Others may have had different encounters, but I believe it is essential to share my unfortunate experience to inform potential customers.
